This project analyzes employee attrition data to identify key factors influencing workforce turnover.
Using Python libraries such as Pandas, NumPy, Seaborn, and Matplotlib, it explores relationships
between attrition and variables like age, years at company, monthly income, and department.

ğŸ” Key Features

Calculates overall attrition rate.
Visualizes attrition patterns using boxplots and countplots.
Compares average age, income, and tenure between employees who left vs. those who stayed.
Examines department-wise attrition trends to find high-risk areas.

ğŸ§° Tools & Technologies

Python (Pandas, NumPy, Seaborn, Matplotlib)
Jupyter Notebook for analysis and visualization
CSV dataset (RR.csv) for employee details

ğŸ’¡ Insights
Younger employees and those with lower income or shorter tenure tend to leave more frequently.
Certain departments experience higher attrition rates, highlighting areas for retention focus.
